---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  path="/work/network-funnel"
  title="Network Funnel — Job Search Analytics | Steven Balalis"
  description="Built networking conversion analytics: outreach → reply → conversation → intro → interview. Job-search tooling designed and shipped end-to-end."
>
  <header class="case-study-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Case study · Built tool</p>
      <h1>Network Funnel</h1>
      <p class="meta">Personal project · Job-search analytics · Networking funnel · Public demo rebuild planned</p>
      <div class="hero-actions" style="margin-top: 1.5rem">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={site.careerOps} rel="noopener">career-ops on GitHub →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="case-study-body">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Context</h2>
      <p>
        Application trackers tell you what you submitted — not whether your networking is converting.
        I scoped a complement: fast capture, funnel dashboard, weekly review.
      </p>

      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>
        Job search networking is hard to measure. Without a funnel view, it's unclear which outreach
        channels and message types lead to conversations and intros.
      </p>

      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        End-to-end builder — problem definition, scope, UX, implementation, and deployment. Shipped a
        working analytics tool alongside my open-source
        <a href={site.careerOps} rel="noopener">career-ops</a> pipeline.
      </p>

      <h2>Approach</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Defined funnel stages: outreach → reply → conversation → intro → interview</li>
        <li>Optimized for fast capture during active search — minimal friction logging</li>
        <li>Built dashboard for weekly review and channel comparison</li>
        <li>Integrated thinking with career-ops for a full job-search workflow</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>
        A shipped artifact that shows technical leadership through building: scoped problem, measurable
        funnel, iterative delivery, and tooling I actually use. The live demo is being rebuilt; the
        case study and <a href={site.careerOps} rel="noopener">career-ops</a> repo are the current
        proof points.
      </p>

      <h2>Artifacts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href={site.careerOps} rel="noopener">career-ops on GitHub</a> — open-source job-search pipeline</li>
        <li><a href={site.github} rel="noopener">GitHub</a> — other technical projects</li>
      </ul>

      <p><a href="/">← Back to portfolio</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
